        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 6:33PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Norias, or near Armstrong, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Norias.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 736 and 746.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
